## 3. DESIGN SYSTEM (Enterprise Light — Strict)
- **Theme:** "Enterprise Light" only. NO dark mode under any circumstance.
- **Backgrounds:** `bg-slate-50` universally.
- **Cards/Surfaces:** `bg-white`, `rounded-2xl`, `border border-slate-200`, `shadow-sm`.
- **Glassmorphism (Executive & HQ only):** Sticky headers → `bg-white/45 backdrop-blur-xl`; KPI cards → `bg-white/55 backdrop-blur-2xl backdrop-saturate-[1.35] ring-1 ring-slate-900/[0.045]`.
- **Icons:** `lucide-react` EXCLUSIVELY. No emojis in UI.
- **Typography:** `font-mono tabular-nums` for all LKR figures. `text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest` for status badges.
- **Status Colors:** Nominal → Emerald, Attention → Amber, Critical → Rose, Accent → Indigo.
- **Field PWA:** Fully responsive, touch-first. Optimised for budget mobile phones on low bandwidth. No glassmorphism.

## 4. DATA FLOW & STATE MANAGEMENT
- **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL). Always import clients from `packages/supabase/` — use `server.ts` in Server Components/Actions, `client.ts` in `'use client'` components, `route.ts` in Route Handlers.
- **Types:** `packages/supabase/types.ts` is **partial and manually maintained** — it only covers `md_settings`, `site_profiles`, `guard_sector_assignments`, and `payroll_deductions`. Do not assume all tables are typed. Inline types where necessary.
- **Mutations:** Use Next.js Server Actions (`'use server'`). Place them in `app/actions/` or co-located alongside the route (`actions.ts` next to `page.tsx`). Do NOT create REST API routes (`app/api/*`) unless integrating external webhooks.
- **Data Fetching:** Fetch server-side in Server Components; pass data as props to Client Components (`'use client'`) for interactivity. Avoid waterfall fetches — run independent queries in `Promise.all`.
- **RBAC:** Middleware enforces route isolation (e.g., `/executive` rejects non-MD/OD tokens). Never rely on client-side role checks alone. Always validate server-side in Server Actions.

